# Read-Before-Write Rule

Before modifying any file:

1. Identify boundaries — JSON analyzer contract, prefs keys, pipeline phase order
2. Read upstream via `@filename` (especially `Core/ClippingClient.lua`, `Orchestrator.lua`)
3. State signatures / contracts in plan
4. Then edit

## Critique checklist

- LR async context (`postAsyncTaskWithContext`, no `pcall` around yields)
- Windows analyzer spawn (see KNOWLEDGE_BASE KB-002)
- Init.lua `require` prohibition (KB-001)
- Dry-run restore of lens + tone settings

## Verification

- Write text files as **UTF-8 without BOM** (never UTF-16 on Windows)
- Never mark BUILD_PLAN tasks complete without running gate scripts
- After scaffold changes: `.\scripts\validate-bootstrap.ps1 -Quick`
- After pipeline changes: `.\scripts\verify-tone-quality.ps1`

Architecture: `docs/adr/0001-core-architecture.md`
